00:25:56,022 --> 00:25:58,922
<font color="yellow">If you don't, I'll report you all for trespassing.</font>

419
00:25:59,452 --> 00:26:00,652
<font color="yellow">Trespassing?</font>

420
00:26:01,052 --> 00:26:03,822
<font color="yellow">We're visiting an in-law. That's not trespassing.</font>

421
00:26:03,922 --> 00:26:05,722
<font color="yellow">We are no longer in-laws.</font>

422
00:26:05,822 --> 00:26:07,452
<font color="yellow">I get it now.</font>

423
00:26:07,452 --> 00:26:10,652
<font color="yellow">You couldn't wait for the two to get divorced.</font>

424
00:26:10,882 --> 00:26:15,722
<font color="yellow">- Where's you conscience? - I did nothing to feel bad about.</font>

425
00:26:17,282 --> 00:26:19,752
<font color="yellow">Did you not? Really?</font>

426
00:26:20,422 --> 00:26:23,922
<font color="yellow">30 years ago. My poor little brother.</font>

427
00:26:24,822 --> 00:26:28,552
<font color="yellow">You went and ruined the life of an innocent and naive young man.</font>

428
00:26:28,852 --> 00:26:31,222
<font color="yellow">And now, you went and ruined Dong Jin's life.</font>

429
00:26:31,422 --> 00:26:33,482
<font color="yellow">What do you have against my family...</font>

430
00:26:33,482 --> 00:26:36,282
<font color="yellow">that you're going after all the men in my life?</font>

431
00:26:36,282 --> 00:26:38,052
<font color="yellow">His death isn't on me!</font>

432
00:26:38,722 --> 00:26:41,522
<font color="yellow">He killed himself because he couldn't handle his own emotions!</font>

433
00:26:41,722 --> 00:26:44,122
<font color="yellow">What did you just say?</font>

434
00:26:44,782 --> 00:26:49,052
<font color="yellow">He killed himself because he couldn't handle his own emotions?</font>

435
00:26:49,052 --> 00:26:50,182
<font color="yellow">Then...</font>

436
00:26:50,882 --> 00:26:52,982
<font color="yellow">are you saying I told him to kill himself?</font>

437
00:26:52,982 --> 00:26:55,322
<font color="yellow">- Is that it? - How dare you.</font>

438
00:26:55,922 --> 00:26:56,982
<font color="yellow">Fine.</font>

439
00:26:57,522 --> 00:27:00,282
<font color="yellow">- Let's fight to the death! - Let go.</font>

440
00:27:00,752 --> 00:27:03,152
<font color="yellow">- Get away from me. - Mum.</font>

441
00:27:04,052 --> 00:27:05,552
<font color="yellow">Did you just push her?</font>

442
00:27:05,922 --> 00:27:07,982
<font color="yellow">She started it.</font>

443
00:27:11,552 --> 00:27:12,652
<font color="yellow">Hey.</font>

444
00:27:14,052 --> 00:27:16,422
<font color="yellow">What are you doing? Let go of me.</font>

445
00:27:17,722 --> 00:27:19,252
<font color="yellow">I was born on a poultry farm,</font>

446
00:27:19,352 --> 00:27:21,682
<font color="yellow">and I've lived around chicken for 45 years.</font>

447
00:27:21,882 --> 00:27:24,952
<font color="yellow">I know a thing or two about plucking feathers.</font>

448
00:27:25,152 --> 00:27:27,422
<font color="yellow">I'll show you what I can do.</font>

449
00:27:27,722 --> 00:27:29,022
<font color="yellow">Don't just stand there.</font>

450
00:27:29,222 --> 00:27:31,582
<font color="yellow">Hurry up and call the police.</font>

451
00:27:31,882 --> 00:27:33,652
<font color="yellow">- Sure thing. Bye. - Let go.</font>

452
00:27:33,782 --> 00:27:35,152
<font color="yellow">- Let go of me. - Go on.</font>

453
00:27:36,882 --> 00:27:38,752
<font color="yellow">- My goodness. - Ms Choi.</font>

454
00:27:39,222 --> 00:27:42,682
<font color="yellow">How much hair should she lose to make you feel better?</font>

455
00:27:43,052 --> 00:27:45,052
<font color="yellow">- Give me a number. - What for?</font>

456
00:27:45,352 --> 00:27:46,522
<font color="yellow">Pull it all out.</font>

457
00:27:46,822 --> 00:27:50,182
<font color="yellow">Okay. A woman who stole someone else's husband...</font>

458
00:27:50,482 --> 00:27:52,322
<font color="yellow">needs a really good lesson.</font>

459
00:27:57,682 --> 00:27:58,782
<font color="yellow">Gosh, my back.</font>

460
00:28:08,952 --> 00:28:10,682
<font color="yellow">The phone has been turned off.</font>

461
00:28:10,682 --> 00:28:13,122
<font color="yellow">- Please leave... - Why won't she pick up?</font>

462
00:28:13,652 --> 00:28:15,422
<font color="yellow">Something bad is happening for sure.</font>

463
00:28:15,982 --> 00:28:18,622
<font color="yellow">Why should she get involved in Dong Jin's business?</font>

464
00:28:19,822 --> 00:28:20,982
<font color="yellow">You're early.</font>

465
00:28:21,352 --> 00:28:23,522
<font color="yellow">Did you get to Anseong and back safely?</font>

466
00:28:23,622 --> 00:28:25,122
<font color="yellow">Yes, thanks to you.</font>

467
00:28:25,382 --> 00:28:27,852
<font color="yellow">- Would you like some coffee? - That would be nice.</font>

468
00:28:28,322 --> 00:28:30,122
<font color="yellow">- I won't be long. - Okay.</font>

469
00:28:34,852 --> 00:28:37,052
<font color="yellow">Dong Jin? It's me, Sam Do.</font>

470
00:28:37,282 --> 00:28:39,722
<font color="yellow">I have bad news. They heard about your divorce.</font>

471
00:28:39,922 --> 00:28:43,152
<font color="yellow">Your mum, Dong Sook and my wife went to your wife's home.</font>

472
00:28:43,952 --> 00:28:44,952
<font color="yellow">Divorce?</font>

473
00:28:59,222 --> 00:29:00,822
<font color="yellow">Here you go.</font>

474
00:29:09,452 --> 00:29:11,482
<font color="yellow">I don't care if we were once in-laws.</font>

475
00:29:12,052 --> 00:29:15,482
<font color="yellow">I'll see a doctor about my injuries and sue you.</font>

476
00:29:16,552 --> 00:29:20,222
<font color="yellow">All three of you are going to jail. Look forward to that.</font>

477
00:29:20,322 --> 00:29:22,052
<font color="yellow">They did nothing wrong.</font>

478
00:29:22,682 --> 00:29:24,522
<font color="yellow">I brought them here.</font>

479
00:29:25,052 --> 00:29:27,622
<font color="yellow">If you want to sue someone, sue me.</font>

480
00:29:28,052 --> 00:29:30,822
<font color="yellow">You're too old to do time.</font>

481
00:29:31,452 --> 00:29:35,152
<font color="yellow">I pulled out all that hair, and I tripped her up.</font>

482
00:29:35,452 --> 00:29:37,052
<font color="yellow">You can sue me.</font>

483
00:29:37,352 --> 00:29:41,052
<font color="yellow">You did nothing wrong. I'm the one who started it.</font>

484
00:29:41,152 --> 00:29:45,152
<font color="yellow">This is all so touching.</font>

485
00:29:45,552 --> 00:29:48,322
<font color="yellow">You three can all go to prison together.</font>

486
00:29:52,182 --> 00:29:54,052
<font color="yellow">- Dong Jin. - Dong Jin.</font>

487
00:29:54,252 --> 00:29:55,852
<font color="yellow">What are you doing here?</font>

488
00:29:56,652 --> 00:29:58,652
<font color="yellow">I won't let this slide.</font>

489
00:29:58,952 --> 00:30:02,752
<font color="yellow">I will get Lawyer Choi to sue them all.</font>

490
00:30:03,422 --> 00:30:04,682
<font color="yellow">Be prepared.</font>

491
00:30:17,722 --> 00:30:19,582
<font color="yellow">She's overreacting.</font>

492
00:30:19,922 --> 00:30:22,052
<font color="yellow">We didn't do that much damage.</font>

493
00:30:23,582 --> 00:30:27,322
<font color="yellow">What should we do now? We made things worse for you.</font>

494
00:30:27,682 --> 00:30:30,552
<font color="yellow">- I didn't think this through. - Get in the car.</font>

495
00:30:43,122 --> 00:30:46,282
<font color="yellow">Don't cry, Mum. You'll make Dong Jin feel bad.</font>

496
00:30:46,482 --> 00:30:48,852
<font color="yellow">I'm a useless mum.</font>

497
00:30:49,182 --> 00:30:51,652
<font color="yellow">Don't blame yourself.</font>

498
00:30:52,552 --> 00:30:54,352
<font color="yellow">It wasn't your fault.</font>

499
00:30:58,022 --> 00:30:59,322
<font color="yellow">Are you saying it's my fault, then?</font>

500
00:30:59,522 --> 00:31:02,822
<font color="yellow">You should've just scared her, not pull out a chunk of hair.</font>

501
00:31:03,022 --> 00:31:05,052
<font color="yellow">She even hurt her back.</font>

502
00:31:05,282 --> 00:31:07,352
<font color="yellow">You can't say that.</font>

503
00:31:07,552 --> 00:31:10,552
<font color="yellow">You told me to pull out all her hair.</font>

504
00:31:10,752 --> 00:31:12,422
<font color="yellow">I was angry at the time.</font>

505
00:31:12,622 --> 00:31:15,152
<font color="yellow">You shouldn't have taken me seriously.</font>

506
00:31:16,152 --> 00:31:18,782
<font color="yellow">I spent all my energy to fight on your behalf.</font>

507
00:31:19,152 --> 00:31:22,822
<font color="yellow">But instead of a thank-you, you blame me for the mess?</font>

508
00:31:22,922 --> 00:31:25,352
<font color="yellow">We shouldn't have brought you along.</font>

509
00:31:25,682 --> 00:31:28,382
<font color="yellow">You fought like an MMA fighter. That was so crass.</font>

510
00:31:28,582 --> 00:31:31,922
<font color="yellow">- Stop saying I'm crass. - Will you two be quiet?</font>

511
00:31:36,652 --> 00:31:40,022
<font color="yellow">Dong Jin's patient and thoughtful.</font>

512
00:31:40,882 --> 00:31:42,982
<font color="yellow">If he decided to get divorced,</font>

513
00:31:43,482 --> 00:31:46,352
<font color="yellow">it means he went through enough to justify it.</font>

514
00:31:48,282 --> 00:31:50,282
<font color="yellow">He took as much as he could handle,</font>

515
00:31:51,152 --> 00:31:55,252
<font color="yellow">and when he'd finally had enough, he gave in.</font>

516
00:31:55,782 --> 00:31:58,182
<font color="yellow">Isn't that what you did?</font>

517
00:31:59,852 --> 00:32:01,482
<font color="yellow">I'm fine, Mum.</font>

518
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:04,982
<font color="yellow">Mum, here.</font>

519
00:32:17,182 --> 00:32:21,722
<font color="yellow">(Wolgyesu Tailor Shop)</font>

520
00:32:22,152 --> 00:32:24,622
<font color="yellow">If we sew it like this instead of using glue...</font>

521
00:32:24,822 --> 00:32:28,152
<font color="yellow">like ready-made suits do, it fits and moves more naturally.</font>

522
00:32:28,652 --> 00:32:32,022
<font color="yellow">And the suit doesn't lose its shape after time.</font>

523
00:32:32,522 --> 00:32:35,052
<font color="yellow">Just like us humans, clothes also have to breathe.</font>

524
00:32:35,522 --> 00:32:38,752
<font color="yellow">Doing this helps air circulate through the fabric...</font>

525
00:32:39,322 --> 00:32:42,322
<font color="yellow">and makes it become more resistant to abrasion.</font>

526
00:32:42,822 --> 00:32:43,822
<font color="yellow">I see.</font>

527
00:32:44,052 --> 00:32:47,322
<font color="yellow">A good suit has to feel three-dimensional.</font>

528
00:32:47,552 --> 00:32:50,722
<font color="yellow">Using the padding stitch technique like this...</font>

529
00:32:50,722 --> 00:32:52,452
<font color="yellow">adds a three-dimensional feel to the suit,</font>

530
00:32:52,452 --> 00:32:55,782
<font color="yellow">which makes the lapel look and feel fuller.</font>

531
00:32:59,622 --> 00:33:00,622
<font color="yellow">Dong Jin.</font>

532
00:33:02,922 --> 00:33:03,922
<font color="yellow">Hello.</font>

533
00:33:04,382 --> 00:33:05,452
<font color="yellow">Hey, how did it go?</font>

534
00:33:05,552 --> 00:33:09,322
<font color="yellow">I just dropped Mum, Dong Sook and Sun Nyeo off at our place.</font>

535
00:33:11,452 --> 00:33:13,322
<font color="yellow">Let's step out for a quick chat, Sam Do.</font>

536
00:33:13,522 --> 00:33:16,382
<font color="yellow">What? There are no customers right now, so we can talk here.</font>

537
00:33:18,222 --> 00:33:20,322
<font color="yellow">- Let's go somewhere quiet. - All right.</font>

538
00:33:21,782 --> 00:33:22,822
<font color="yellow">I'll be back shortly.</font>

539
00:33:22,922 --> 00:33:23,952
<font color="yellow">Okay.</font>

540
00:33:27,682 --> 00:33:29,782
<font color="yellow">Is he worried that I'd eavesdrop on their conversation?</font>

541
00:33:30,182 --> 00:33:32,222
<font color="yellow">I have no interest in your business, okay?</font>

542
00:33:40,722 --> 00:33:42,152
<font color="yellow">How is Ms Choi holding up?</font>

543
00:33:43,652 --> 00:33:44,682
<font color="yellow">She's upset, of course.</font>

544
00:33:44,882 --> 00:33:47,882
<font color="yellow">Frankly, I think about getting divorced a dozen times a day.</font>

545
00:33:48,182 --> 00:33:50,182
<font color="yellow">But as you know, getting divorced isn't that simple.</font>

546
00:33:50,922 --> 00:33:52,482
<font color="yellow">Consider all factors carefully.</font>

547
00:33:52,582 --> 00:33:53,852
<font color="yellow">To her, I was...</font>

548
00:33:54,882 --> 00:33:56,252
<font color="yellow">never really a husband.</font>

549
00:33:56,782 --> 00:33:58,052
<font color="yellow">I think she just...</font>

550
00:33:58,652 --> 00:34:00,922
<font color="yellow">thought of me as her guardian or butler.</font>

551
00:34:01,182 --> 00:34:03,822
<font color="yellow">No, you're being too cynical. She'd never think of you as...</font>

552
00:34:03,922 --> 00:34:05,322
<font color="yellow">I can't tell you all the details,</font>

553
00:34:05,882 --> 00:34:07,892
<font color="yellow">but she's made me feel that way throughout our marriage.</font>

554
00:34:08,052 --> 00:34:09,352
<font color="yellow">It sounds like you're exhausted.</font>

555
00:34:10,052 --> 00:34:11,122
<font color="yellow">Yes.</font>

556
00:34:11,852 --> 00:34:14,482
<font color="yellow">I want to be free now.</font>

557
00:34:14,722 --> 00:34:17,052
<font color="yellow">I want to free myself from my greed and ambition...</font>

558
00:34:17,522 --> 00:34:20,392
<font color="yellow">and leave her in order to find peace of mind.</font>

559
00:34:22,482 --> 00:34:23,482
<font color="yellow">All right.</font>

560
00:34:25,982 --> 00:34:27,422
<font color="yellow">I actually...</font>

561
00:34:28,652 --> 00:34:29,952
<font color="yellow">met up with my dad last night.</font>

562
00:34:30,352 --> 00:34:31,982
<font color="yellow">You met up with Mr Lee? How?</font>

563
00:34:32,582 --> 00:34:34,722
<font color="yellow">I managed to talk to him on the phone, and we met up.</font>

564
00:34:35,422 --> 00:34:36,482
<font color="yellow">Then...</font>

565
00:34:37,392 --> 00:34:38,822
<font color="yellow">you should've brought him home.</font>

566
00:34:39,122 --> 00:34:42,552
<font color="yellow">You know how stubborn he is. I couldn't persuade him.</font>

567
00:34:42,652 --> 00:34:43,952
<font color="yellow">Then you should've called me!</font>

568
00:34:44,252 --> 00:34:45,652
<font color="yellow">Is he okay?</font>

569
00:34:48,922 --> 00:34:50,682
<font color="yellow">Please keep my illness a secret...</font>

570
00:34:51,222 --> 00:34:55,252
<font color="yellow">until I come home and tell them myself.</font>

571
00:34:55,622 --> 00:34:56,922
<font color="yellow">Do me a favour.</font>

572
00:34:58,922 --> 00:35:00,852
<font color="yellow">Yes. He seemed to be doing all right.</font>

573
00:35:01,782 --> 00:35:05,022
<font color="yellow">He was happy to hear about you working as a tailor again.</font>

574
00:35:05,522 --> 00:35:08,452
<font color="yellow">He told me to tell you how grateful he is.</font>

575
00:35:09,952 --> 00:35:10,982
<font color="yellow">Goodness.</font>

576
00:35:11,652 --> 00:35:14,352
<font color="yellow">I should've been there to see him. I'm sad I wasn't there.</font>

577
00:35:14,652 --> 00:35:18,122
<font color="yellow">I was surprised because he looked so happy.</font>

578
00:35:19,422 --> 00:35:21,252
<font color="yellow">I've never seen him looking that content.</font>

579
00:35:22,682 --> 00:35:25,222
<font color="yellow">He said he's been wandering around and working without a proper home,</font>

580
00:35:25,892 --> 00:35:29,482
<font color="yellow">so I thought he'd be extremely exhausted, but I was wrong.</font>

581
00:35:31,182 --> 00:35:32,682
<font color="yellow">What exactly do suits...</font>

582
00:35:33,782 --> 00:35:34,852
<font color="yellow">mean to him?</font>

583
00:35:34,952 --> 00:35:36,122
<font color="yellow">Mr Lee...</font>

584
00:35:39,582 --> 00:35:41,322
<font color="yellow">doesn't just make suits.</font>

585
00:35:42,782 --> 00:35:44,122
<font color="yellow">He builds lives.</font>

586
00:35:45,852 --> 00:35:49,222
<font color="yellow">I'm not sure how you view him, but he isn't...</font>

587
00:35:50,252 --> 00:35:53,582
<font color="yellow">a mere tailor. He's a philosopher.</font>

588
00:35:54,852 --> 00:35:56,052
<font color="yellow">That's what I think at least.</font>

589
00:35:58,452 --> 00:35:59,952
<font color="yellow">Is making suits...</font>

590
00:36:01,222 --> 00:36:04,392
<font color="yellow">that much of a grand job? You're comparing it to building lives.</font>

591
00:36:04,582 --> 00:36:06,552
<font color="yellow">I'm not sure if I can say that it's grand,</font>

592
00:36:08,752 --> 00:36:10,582
<font color="yellow">but the job certainly makes you happy.</font>

593
00:36:11,682 --> 00:36:14,952
<font color="yellow">I'll be sure to become a tailor again in my next life.</font>

594
00:36:18,322 --> 00:36:20,052
<font color="yellow">If I work at the tailor shop,</font>

595
00:36:21,392 --> 00:36:22,522
<font color="yellow">will I...</font>

596
00:36:23,892 --> 00:36:25,552
<font color="yellow">also be happy?</font>

597
00:36:26,182 --> 00:36:28,892
<font color="yellow">Dong Jin, you want to work at the tailor shop?</font>

598
00:36:32,352 --> 00:36:34,782
<font color="yellow">People swarmed over like bees yesterday,</font>

599
00:36:35,052 --> 00:36:36,682
<font color="yellow">but today was pretty horrible.</font>

600
00:36:37,252 --> 00:36:38,952
<font color="yellow">I didn't even make enough for a burger.</font>

601
00:36:39,352 --> 00:36:41,952
<font color="yellow">Mr Kang, please do something.</font>

602
00:36:42,422 --> 00:36:43,722
<font color="yellow">What do you want me to do?</font>

603
00:36:44,122 --> 00:36:46,252
<font color="yellow">I've been out of that industry for over a decade.</font>

604
00:36:46,622 --> 00:36:50,522
<font color="yellow">Right, so come back and work with me.</font>

605
00:36:51,052 --> 00:36:52,452
<font color="yellow">We used to be such a great team.</font>

606
00:36:52,652 --> 00:36:55,352
<font color="yellow">After you fell hard for that woman and ran away to the States,</font>

607
00:36:55,552 --> 00:36:58,482
<font color="yellow">our agency had to pay the penalties for breaking all the contracts.</font>

608
00:36:58,582 --> 00:36:59,652
<font color="yellow">You know all that.</font>

609
00:36:59,752 --> 00:37:01,582
<font color="yellow">How can you say that we were a great team?</font>

610
00:37:01,852 --> 00:37:02,982
<font color="yellow">Back then, I was...</font>

611
00:37:03,952 --> 00:37:05,422
<font color="yellow">I was immature then.</font>

612
00:37:06,052 --> 00:37:07,552
<font color="yellow">That will never happen again.</font>

613
00:37:08,782 --> 00:37:11,852
<font color="yellow">I'll make sure there are no scandals whatsoever. So please...</font>

614
00:37:11,852 --> 00:37:13,982
<font color="yellow">I'll give you a call when I hear of any events you can perform at.</font>

615
00:37:14,052 --> 00:37:15,052
<font color="yellow">I have to go. Bye.</font>

616
00:37:15,052 --> 00:37:16,352
<font color="yellow">Mr Kang. Hey.</font>

617
00:37:23,422 --> 00:37:25,222
<font color="yellow">Shall I look for a new agency?</font>

618
00:37:25,452 --> 00:37:27,392
<font color="yellow">The job I did yesterday was sweet.</font>

619
00:37:27,552 --> 00:37:28,722
<font color="yellow">What was it?</font>

620
00:37:28,952 --> 00:37:30,252
<font color="yellow">What was his name?</font>

621
00:37:30,952 --> 00:37:34,392
<font color="yellow">He used to be a famous singer. I went to his busking performance...</font>

622
00:37:34,682 --> 00:37:37,952
<font color="yellow">and screamed and cheered for him for an hour.</font>

623
00:37:38,682 --> 00:37:39,952
<font color="yellow">I got 50 dollars for it.</font>

624
00:37:41,722 --> 00:37:44,122
<font color="yellow">- My goodness. That's a sweet job. - That woman...</font>

625
00:37:44,452 --> 00:37:45,952
<font color="yellow">came to my performance yesterday.</font>

626
00:37:46,052 --> 00:37:47,052
<font color="yellow">How was the performance?</font>

627
00:37:47,182 --> 00:37:48,222
<font color="yellow">It was horrible.</font>

628
00:37:48,322 --> 00:37:50,482
<font color="yellow">Was it that bad? What's his name?</font>

629
00:37:52,352 --> 00:37:53,652
<font color="yellow">What was it?</font>

630
00:37:54,482 --> 00:37:56,052
<font color="yellow">I think it was a two-syllable name.</font>

631
00:37:57,482 --> 00:37:58,522
<font color="yellow">Sung Jun.</font>

632
00:37:58,522 --> 00:37:59,622
<font color="yellow">Yes, Sung Jun.</font>

633
00:38:00,452 --> 00:38:01,522
<font color="yellow">My goodness!</font>

634
00:38:02,722 --> 00:38:04,522
<font color="yellow">Who gave you that job?</font>

635
00:38:05,782 --> 00:38:08,722
<font color="yellow">I've been neglecting my store because of Jun.</font>

636
00:38:08,922 --> 00:38:11,122
<font color="yellow">I guess that's why I don't see a single soul here.</font>

637
00:38:11,982 --> 00:38:14,052
<font color="yellow">Shall I run some sort of promotional events?</font>

638
00:38:16,752 --> 00:38:19,682
<font color="yellow">Hi, Jun! What brings you here at this hour?</font>

639
00:38:20,122 --> 00:38:21,582
<font color="yellow">Is your performance already done?</font>

640
00:38:22,852 --> 00:38:24,182
<font color="yellow">Do you think I'm a joke?</font>

641
00:38:24,392 --> 00:38:26,422
<font color="yellow">What are you talking about?</font>

642
00:38:26,422 --> 00:38:29,222
<font color="yellow">I heard that you paid those people who came...</font>

643
00:38:30,022 --> 00:38:31,322
<font color="yellow">to watch my performance.</font>

644
00:38:31,652 --> 00:38:34,782
<font color="yellow">- Who said such nonsense? - I heard it...</font>

645
00:38:35,322 --> 00:38:38,222
<font color="yellow">directly from one of the people you hired, so don't even try to lie.</font>

646
00:38:39,152 --> 00:38:41,852
<font color="yellow">Well... I'm sorry, Jun.</font>

647
00:38:42,482 --> 00:38:44,522
<font color="yellow">I didn't mean to upset you or anything.</font>

648
00:38:44,752 --> 00:38:47,682
<font color="yellow">I couldn't bear to watch you performing with no audience.</font>

649
00:38:47,892 --> 00:38:49,752
<font color="yellow">I just wanted to cheer you up...</font>

650
00:38:51,182 --> 00:38:54,452
<font color="yellow">Why do you make me feel so pathetic?</font>

651
00:38:54,452 --> 00:38:57,682
<font color="yellow">Why do you feel pathetic? I wanted to encourage you.</font>

652
00:38:57,682 --> 00:38:58,782
<font color="yellow">I'm...</font>

653
00:38:59,522 --> 00:39:02,892
<font color="yellow">not pathetic enough to need your pity.</font>

654
00:39:03,682 --> 00:39:04,822
<font color="yellow">This is a warning!</font>

655
00:39:05,722 --> 00:39:07,322
<font color="yellow">Do not meddle in my business ever again.</font>

656
00:39:08,522 --> 00:39:09,622
<font color="yellow">Got it?</font>

657
00:39:13,152 --> 00:39:14,622
<font color="yellow">Jun, Jun!</font>

658
00:39:16,222 --> 00:39:17,282
<font color="yellow">Hello.</font>

659
00:39:21,582 --> 00:39:23,582
<font color="yellow">I knew it. I was wondering what was going on.</font>

660
00:39:23,892 --> 00:39:26,252
<font color="yellow">I was a fool to let myself get all excited about it.</font>

661
00:39:28,352 --> 00:39:29,392
<font color="yellow">Excuse me.</font>

662
00:39:30,022 --> 00:39:31,152
<font color="yellow">Aren't you...</font>

663
00:39:31,622 --> 00:39:33,252
<font color="yellow">Mr Sung Jun?</font>

664
00:39:34,152 --> 00:39:35,552
<font color="yellow">Who are you?</font>

665
00:39:40,682 --> 00:39:44,152
<font color="yellow">I'm the executive director of Hyesung Entertainment, Oh Chang Soo.</font>

666
00:39:44,622 --> 00:39:45,682
<font color="yellow">Why did you want to speak to me?</font>

667
00:39:45,782 --> 00:39:48,322
<font color="yellow">Mr Oh really wanted to meet with you after hearing that you're back...</font>

668
00:39:48,322 --> 00:39:52,252
<font color="yellow">in Korea now working on making a comeback.</font>

669
00:39:52,422 --> 00:39:54,752
<font color="yellow">We heard that your office is in this area,</font>

670
00:39:54,982 --> 00:39:57,352
<font color="yellow">so we've been looking all over for you for a few days now.</font>

671
00:39:57,852 --> 00:39:59,182
<font color="yellow">Then are you...</font>

672
00:40:00,482 --> 00:40:02,892
<font color="yellow">here to offer me a contract?</font>

673
00:40:02,982 --> 00:40:04,252
<font color="yellow">Of course.</font>

674
00:40:04,352 --> 00:40:07,652
<font color="yellow">You took the music scene by storm as soon as you debuted 15 years ago.</font>

675
00:40:07,922 --> 00:40:10,152
<font color="yellow">Then you disappeared like the wind at the peak of your prime.</font>

676
00:40:10,622 --> 00:40:13,152
<font color="yellow">I was a huge fan of yours, so it utterly broke my heart.</font>

677
00:40:15,052 --> 00:40:18,152
<font color="yellow">That was the biggest mistake of my life.</font>

678
00:40:18,392 --> 00:40:20,622
<font color="yellow">You're back now, and you want to make a comeback.</font>

679
00:40:21,052 --> 00:40:23,752
<font color="yellow">I have to be the one producing your new album.</font>

680
00:40:25,222 --> 00:40:26,482
<font color="yellow">It's very nice to meet you.</font>

681
00:40:42,052 --> 00:40:44,582
<font color="yellow">The payment for your student loan is overdue.</font>

682
00:40:44,682 --> 00:40:48,322
<font color="yellow">If you fail to make the payment, it could affect your credit rating.</font>

683
00:40:48,422 --> 00:40:50,552
<font color="yellow">- Please make the payment soon. - It's overdue?</font>

684
00:40:52,282 --> 00:40:53,752
<font color="yellow">Is it already past the deadline?</font>

685
00:40:54,022 --> 00:40:56,982
<font color="yellow">So you'd like to see if the deadline can be extended?</font>

686
00:40:57,052 --> 00:40:58,952
<font color="yellow">Yes. I haven't found a job yet.</font>

687
00:41:00,052 --> 00:41:03,322
<font color="yellow">But I see that you've already extended it once.</font>

688
00:41:03,482 --> 00:41:06,682
<font color="yellow">Only one deadline extension is allowed per person,</font>

689
00:41:06,682 --> 00:41:08,352
<font color="yellow">so it cannot be extended further.</font>

690
00:41:08,522 --> 00:41:10,922
<font color="yellow">I'm unable to pay the interest and the minimum payment right now.</font>

691
00:41:10,922 --> 00:41:12,152
<font color="yellow">Is there anything you can do?</font>

692
00:41:12,152 --> 00:41:13,252
<font color="yellow">I'm sorry.</font>

693
00:41:26,452 --> 00:41:27,622
<font color="yellow">What now?</font>

694
00:41:27,852 --> 00:41:29,522
<font color="yellow">You're so cold.</font>

695
00:41:30,422 --> 00:41:34,452
<font color="yellow">We haven't talked in a while. Can you be a little warmer towards me?</font>

696
00:41:34,552 --> 00:41:36,852
<font color="yellow">Hang up unless you have something specific to talk about.</font>

697
00:41:36,952 --> 00:41:39,252
<font color="yellow">No! Don't hang up. I'm calling you for a reason.</font>

698
00:41:39,452 --> 00:41:41,052
<font color="yellow">- What is it? - I'm off tomorrow.</font>

699
00:41:41,252 --> 00:41:42,392
<font color="yellow">Let's go to the movies together.</font>

700
00:41:42,482 --> 00:41:44,582
<font color="yellow">I'll buy lunch as well as popcorn.</font>

701
00:41:44,952 --> 00:41:46,022
<font color="yellow">I'm busy.</font>

702
00:41:46,122 --> 00:41:48,322
<font color="yellow">Why are you always so busy when you don't even have a job?</font>

703
00:41:48,522 --> 00:41:50,922
<font color="yellow">Unemployed people are busier than employed ones. Bye.</font>

704
00:41:52,222 --> 00:41:55,782
<font color="yellow">Wait, Tae Yang. Don't hang up. Hello? Tae Yang?</font>

705
00:41:57,982 --> 00:41:59,552
<font color="yellow">I guess he's still trying to be hard to get.</font>

706
00:41:59,652 --> 00:42:02,982
<font color="yellow">Gosh, you startled me. Did you just eavesdrop on my conversation?</font>

707
00:42:04,352 --> 00:42:05,752
<font color="yellow">It wasn't intentional.</font>

708
00:42:05,852 --> 00:42:07,952
<font color="yellow">I was walking here and overheard it.</font>

709
00:42:08,922 --> 00:42:11,252
<font color="yellow">So is he still being hard to get?</font>

710
00:42:12,452 --> 00:42:13,922
<font color="yellow">He's being so difficult.</font>

711
00:42:14,022 --> 00:42:17,622
<font color="yellow">Who is he? How can he treat someone like you that way?</font>

712
00:42:18,052 --> 00:42:20,482
<font color="yellow">It even sounded like he's jobless right now.</font>

713
00:42:20,682 --> 00:42:22,852
<font color="yellow">So many young people are unemployed these days.</font>

714
00:42:23,852 --> 00:42:26,852
<font color="yellow">He's doing his best to get a job, so I'm sure he'll land one soon.</font>

715
00:42:26,952 --> 00:42:28,682
<font color="yellow">Had I known that he'd stay unemployed for this long,</font>

716
00:42:28,922 --> 00:42:32,152
<font color="yellow">I would've helped him when you asked me.</font>

717
00:42:32,352 --> 00:42:33,952
<font color="yellow">No thanks.</font>

718
00:42:36,282 --> 00:42:38,222
<font color="yellow">What's the point in saying that now?</font>

719
00:42:38,522 --> 00:42:39,652
<font color="yellow">Whatever.</font>

720
00:42:40,982 --> 00:42:42,552
<font color="yellow">How's your grandmother?</font>

721
00:42:43,352 --> 00:42:44,782
<font color="yellow">She took some pills and is resting.</font>

722
00:42:45,182 --> 00:42:47,082
<font color="yellow">How's your mother? Did she go to the hospital?</font>

723
00:42:47,322 --> 00:42:49,152
<font color="yellow">She got checked out, but there's nothing wrong with her.</font>

724
00:42:49,482 --> 00:42:50,922
<font color="yellow">She exaggerates a lot.</font>

725
00:42:52,182 --> 00:42:55,022
<font color="yellow">By the way, if my sister and your uncle get a divorce,</font>

726
00:42:55,322 --> 00:42:58,322
<font color="yellow">does that mean our friendship is over?</font>

727
00:42:58,522 --> 00:43:01,952
<font color="yellow">- What friendship? - What?</font>

728
00:43:02,552 --> 00:43:04,752
<font color="yellow">I thought we became really close.</font>

729
00:43:05,182 --> 00:43:06,222
<font color="yellow">Was I wrong?</font>

730
00:43:06,222 --> 00:43:09,352
<font color="yellow">I don't think we're that close,</font>

731
00:43:09,822 --> 00:43:12,952
<font color="yellow">but I won't hold grudges even if they get divorced.</font>

732
00:43:13,822 --> 00:43:17,022
<font color="yellow">- That's a relief. - Let's go back in now.</font>

733
00:43:18,452 --> 00:43:19,522
<font color="yellow">Sit here.</font>

734
00:43:22,122 --> 00:43:26,022
<font color="yellow">I told you not to take a picture since I don't have makeup on.</font>

735
00:43:26,322 --> 00:43:29,052
<font color="yellow">- Why did you take a picture? - I'm sorry.</font>

736
00:43:29,452 --> 00:43:31,322
<font color="yellow">I have a friend who wants to be an announcer.</font>

737
00:43:31,522 --> 00:43:33,452
<font color="yellow">You're her role model.</font>

738
00:43:34,052 --> 00:43:37,222
<font color="yellow">- She wanted a picture of you. - That's none of my business.</font>

739
00:43:37,522 --> 00:43:40,152
<font color="yellow">That's a violation of my portrait rights.</font>

740
00:43:40,352 --> 00:43:43,822
<font color="yellow">Aren't you supposed to know that?</font>

741
00:43:44,052 --> 00:43:46,522
<font color="yellow">- She's the person who tripped me. - That's her.</font>

742
00:43:46,722 --> 00:43:49,482
<font color="yellow">Choi Ji Yun of KBC. She's so rude.</font>

743
00:43:51,822 --> 00:43:53,422
<font color="yellow">I'm sorry.</font>

744
00:43:53,522 --> 00:43:55,282
<font color="yellow">It's her first day at work.</font>

745
00:43:55,382 --> 00:43:59,252
<font color="yellow">She wasn't aware of our system. It was an honest mistake.</font>

746
00:43:59,622 --> 00:44:01,722
<font color="yellow">I'll knock some sense into her.</font>

747
00:44:01,822 --> 00:44:03,652
<font color="yellow">That won't cut it.</font>

748
00:44:03,852 --> 00:44:07,382
<font color="yellow">Who would come to this place if you invade people's privacy like this?</font>

749
00:44:07,722 --> 00:44:10,482
<font color="yellow">I'm sorry. It won't happen again.</font>

750
00:44:10,982 --> 00:44:12,552
<font color="yellow">I'm really sorry.</font>

751
00:44:12,652 --> 00:44:16,252
<font color="yellow">This is common sense. This isn't some local barber shop.</font>

752
00:44:19,822 --> 00:44:20,922
<font color="yellow">What?</font>

753
00:44:23,782 --> 00:44:27,022
<font color="yellow">Hey, you. She says it's her first day at work.</font>

754
00:44:27,452 --> 00:44:30,152
<font color="yellow">It was an honest mistake. What's the big deal?</font>

755
00:44:30,452 --> 00:44:31,582
<font color="yellow">Come on.</font>

756
00:44:31,952 --> 00:44:35,782
<font color="yellow">If you don't want people taking pictures of you, quit your job.</font>

757
00:44:36,152 --> 00:44:38,982
<font color="yellow">- Then nobody will be interested. - What did you say?</font>

758
00:44:38,982 --> 00:44:42,822
<font color="yellow">You look the same with or without makeup anyway.</font>

759
00:44:43,582 --> 00:44:44,682
<font color="yellow">Stop making a fuss.</font>

760
00:44:45,452 --> 00:44:47,622
<font color="yellow">- Are you done talking? - Yes.</font>

761
00:44:47,982 --> 00:44:50,182
<font color="yellow">- Did you want to hear some more? - Excuse me?</font>

762
00:44:50,382 --> 00:44:53,152
<font color="yellow">- I have to shampoo my hair. - This way.</font>

763
00:44:56,182 --> 00:44:57,922
<font color="yellow">What a crazy woman.</font>

764
00:44:59,052 --> 00:45:00,322
<font color="yellow">(Min Hyo Sang)</font>

765
00:45:02,382 --> 00:45:04,322
<font color="yellow">- It's me. - I'm really sorry.</font>

766
00:45:04,722 --> 00:45:06,352
<font color="yellow">I can't make it tonight.</font>

767
00:45:06,552 --> 00:45:08,952
<font color="yellow">Why not? Is there trouble at the office?</font>

768
00:45:09,152 --> 00:45:12,652
<font color="yellow">My mum's sick. I think I should go see her.</font>

769
00:45:12,852 --> 00:45:14,052
<font color="yellow">Is it serious?</font>

770
00:45:14,582 --> 00:45:16,052
<font color="yellow">It's not that serious.</font>

771
00:45:16,822 --> 00:45:18,352
<font color="yellow">I think she strained her back.</font>

772
00:45:18,452 --> 00:45:21,152
<font color="yellow">It's okay with me. Look after your mother.</font>

773
00:45:23,222 --> 00:45:25,122
<font color="yellow">Okay, call me later.</font>

774
00:45:30,682 --> 00:45:33,482
<font color="yellow">I thought he was going to propose to me tonight.</font>

775
00:45:34,452 --> 00:45:37,022
<font color="yellow">Come to think of it, why is he always talking about his mum?</font>

776
00:45:38,182 --> 00:45:39,752
<font color="yellow">Is he some kind of mummy's boy?</font>

777
00:45:44,152 --> 00:45:45,522
<font color="yellow">You're here.</font>

778
00:45:46,552 --> 00:45:49,382
<font color="yellow">You should go to the hospital. What are you doing here?</font>

779
00:45:49,382 --> 00:45:53,482
<font color="yellow">Doctor Kim said I'll be okay if I rest for a few days.</font>

780
00:45:53,482 --> 00:45:55,182
<font color="yellow">How can Ms Choi be like that?</font>

781
00:45:55,422 --> 00:45:57,122
<font color="yellow">She even splashed juice on you last time.</font>

782
00:45:57,482 --> 00:46:01,582
<font color="yellow">We need to teach her a lesson. Let's sue her.</font>

783
00:46:02,282 --> 00:46:05,982
<font color="yellow">We're in-laws after all. That would be too much.</font>

784
00:46:06,052 --> 00:46:08,782
<font color="yellow">Hyo Joo and Dong Jin are about to get a divorce. You're not in-laws.</font>

785
00:46:09,122 --> 00:46:13,922
<font color="yellow">Even then, once in-laws are forever in-laws.</font>

786
00:46:15,022 --> 00:46:16,522
<font color="yellow">You're weird.</font>

787
00:46:17,152 --> 00:46:20,252
<font color="yellow">Why are you always so scared of Ms Choi?</font>

788
00:46:20,452 --> 00:46:22,322
<font color="yellow">- What does she have on you? - There's no such thing.</font>

789
00:46:22,822 --> 00:46:24,752
<font color="yellow">Do I look like someone who lets people do that to me?</font>

790
00:46:28,122 --> 00:46:29,552
<font color="yellow">My back.</font>

791
00:46:30,782 --> 00:46:32,722
<font color="yellow">Oh, my head.</font>

792
00:46:39,782 --> 00:46:42,252
<font color="yellow">- They didn't call you, did they? - Who?</font>

793
00:46:42,452 --> 00:46:43,822
<font color="yellow">You know who.</font>

794
00:46:45,152 --> 00:46:47,582
<font color="yellow">- I'm talking about Ms Ko. - Why?</font>

795
00:46:47,922 --> 00:46:49,222
<font color="yellow">Are you afraid she might sue you?</font>

796
00:46:49,322 --> 00:46:51,382
<font color="yellow">She can't sue me.</font>

797
00:46:51,482 --> 00:46:53,782
<font color="yellow">After everything she's done to me.</font>

798
00:46:54,022 --> 00:46:57,182
<font color="yellow">Where is Dong Jin during all this?</font>

799
00:46:57,282 --> 00:47:00,222
<font color="yellow">- Call him up. - Fine.</font>

800
00:47:06,382 --> 00:47:08,182
<font color="yellow">Hey, Dong Sook. How's Mum?</font>

801
00:47:08,382 --> 00:47:11,622
<font color="yellow">What do you think? She's sick in bed.</font>

802
00:47:12,282 --> 00:47:15,022
<font color="yellow">- Where are you? - I'm at a hotel.</font>

803
00:47:15,552 --> 00:47:18,552
<font color="yellow">- He says he's at a hotel. - What's he doing there?</font>

804
00:47:18,652 --> 00:47:19,852
<font color="yellow">Give me the phone.</font>

805
00:47:21,982 --> 00:47:24,022
<font color="yellow">- It's your mother. - Hey, Mum.</font>

806
00:47:24,282 --> 00:47:26,322
<font color="yellow">I was about to call you.</font>

807
00:47:26,652 --> 00:47:29,422
<font color="yellow">Why are you at a hotel when you can stay at home?</font>

808
00:47:29,722 --> 00:47:31,722
<font color="yellow">You should come to me.</font>

809
00:47:32,922 --> 00:47:36,352
<font color="yellow">I'll make doenjang jjigae, your favourite.</font>

810
00:47:36,652 --> 00:47:37,782
<font color="yellow">Hurry back home.</font>

811
00:47:38,052 --> 00:47:40,122
<font color="yellow">Why would you eat outside?</font>

812
00:47:43,052 --> 00:47:44,552
<font color="yellow">Why aren't you saying anything?</font>

813
00:47:45,882 --> 00:47:48,782
<font color="yellow">- Dong Jin. - Yes, Mum. I'll be on my way.</font>

814
00:47:48,982 --> 00:47:52,052
<font color="yellow">Okay, hurry back. I'll be waiting for you.</font>

815
00:47:56,782 --> 00:48:00,252
<font color="yellow">Dong Jin is better than pills. He got that headband off.</font>

816
00:48:00,452 --> 00:48:03,022
<font color="yellow">Go to the grocery store and get me some chadolbagi.</font>

817
00:48:03,222 --> 00:48:04,682
<font color="yellow">What do you need chadolbagi for?</font>

818
00:48:04,882 --> 00:48:08,782
<font color="yellow">Dong Jin loves chadolbagi in his doenjang jjigae.</font>

819
00:48:09,282 --> 00:48:12,822
<font color="yellow">Don't get frozen chadolbagi. Get the highest quality ones.</font>

820
00:48:18,152 --> 00:48:21,052
<font color="yellow">Sung Jun is probably drinking by himself.</font>

821
00:48:22,482 --> 00:48:26,352
<font color="yellow">- Hurry, Dong Sook. - I'm going.</font>

822
00:48:27,522 --> 00:48:29,382
<font color="yellow">The fabric is the flesh.</font>

823
00:48:29,682 --> 00:48:31,682
<font color="yellow">The thread is the bone.</font>

824
00:48:32,452 --> 00:48:35,922
<font color="yellow">Then if you want to make clothes that fit the body perfectly,</font>

825
00:48:36,322 --> 00:48:37,882
<font color="yellow">you'll need to do a lot of needlework, right?</font>

826
00:48:38,282 --> 00:48:40,682
